  "eprint": {
    "title": "Fast algebraic immunity of Boolean functions and LCD codes",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Sihem Mesnager",
        "email": "tangchunmingmath@163",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Chunming Tang",
        "email": "",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "Nowadays, the resistance against algebraic attacks and fast algebraic\nattacks are considered as an important cryptographic property for\nBoolean functions used in stream ciphers. Both attacks are very\npowerful analysis concepts and can be applied to symmetric\ncryptographic algorithms used in stream ciphers.\nThe notion of algebraic immunity has received wide attention since\nit is a powerful tool to measure the resistance of a Boolean function\nto standard algebraic attacks. Nevertheless, an algebraic tool to\nhandle the resistance to fast algebraic attacks is not clearly\nidentified in the literature. In the current paper, we propose a new\nparameter to measure the resistance of a Boolean function to fast\nalgebraic attack. We also introduce the notion of fast immunity profile and\nshow that it informs both on the resistance to standard and fast\nalgebraic attacks. Further, we evaluate our parameter for two\nsecondary constructions of Boolean functions.\nMoreover, A coding-theory approach to the characterization of perfect algebraic immune functions is presented.\nVia this characterization, infinite families of binary linear complementary dual codes (or LCD codes for short) are obtained from perfect algebraic immune functions.\nThe binary LCD codes presented in this paper have applications in armoring implementations against\nso-called side-channel attacks (SCA) and fault non-invasive attacks, in addition to their applications in communication and data storage systems.",
    "keywords": [
      "Boolean function",
      "(Fast) Algebraic immunity",
      "Algebraic attack",
      "Fast algebraic attack",
      "Fault injection attack Side-channel attack",
      "LCD code",
      "Reed-Muller code"
    ],
    "category": "Secret-key cryptography",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2020-06-16",
